{
  "text": "Consistent with previous data in rats [CITATION_1] , breathing persisted when B+S were injected bilaterally into the preB\u00f6 tC of adult mice with intact vagus nerves. Relative to control values, f decreased to 38% \u00b1 1% (p = 0.0001, n = 5), T I increased to 142% \u00b1 15% (p = 0.03, n = 5), and T E increased to 305% \u00b1 17% (p = 0.0001, n = 5; Figures 6A and 6B ). B+S also affected GG EMG burst shape ( Figure 6A ). GG EMG burst amplitude increased to 490% \u00b1 26% (p = 10 \u00c05 , n = 5; Figure 6B ), and tidal volume (V T ) increased to 309% \u00b1 44% (p = 10",
